[size=14pt][b]🌟 What's New in v0.0.8-0.0.9-beta[/b][/size]

[size=12pt][b]1. Quantum Privacy Mixer - Zero-Knowledge Transaction Privacy[/b][/size]

The centerpiece of this release: a production-ready privacy mixer with [b]ZK-STARK proofs[/b] that completely hides transaction details.

[b]Privacy Technology:[/b]
• [b]ZK-STARK Proofs[/b] - Hide sender, recipient, and amount in ALL transactions
• [b]Ring Signatures[/b] - Sign transactions on behalf of a group for plausible deniability
• [b]Stealth Addresses[/b] - One-time addresses that cannot be linked to recipients
• [b]Decoy Routing[/b] - Obfuscate transaction paths through the network
• [b]Post-Quantum Secure[/b] - Dilithium5 signatures resist quantum attacks

[b]Privacy Levels:[/b]
[code]Standard (15s):  Basic privacy, fast confirmation
High (30s):      Enhanced anonymity, ring size 50
Maximum (60s):   Maximum privacy, full decoy routing[/code]

[b]How It Works:[/b]
1. User sends transaction through mixer with privacy level selection
2. System generates ZK-STARK proof hiding transaction details
3. Funds mixed with decoy transactions over configurable time period
4. Recipient receives funds from unlinked address
5. Complete privacy - even blockchain explorers can't trace the flow

[b]Frontend Integration:[/b]
• Beautiful 3D visualization showing mixing progress
• Real-time updates via Server-Sent Events (SSE)
• Automatic balance refresh after mixing completes
• Privacy guarantee message explaining ZK-STARK technology

[b]Recent Critical Fixes:[/b]
• [b]Address Parsing Bug (Oct 25)[/b] - Fixed "qnk" prefix handling that was sending funds to wrong addresses
• [b]SSE Buffer Overflow[/b] - Increased event buffer from 10k to 100k to prevent dropped balance updates during high mining activity

[hr]

[size=12pt][b]2. Privacy-as-a-Service (PaaS) - Enterprise-Grade Cross-Chain Privacy[/b][/size]

Q-NarwhalKnight now offers [b]blockchain-agnostic privacy infrastructure[/b] that works with Bitcoin, Ethereum, Solana, and any other blockchain.

[b]Key Features:[/b]
• ✅ [b]Cross-Chain Support[/b] - Universal privacy API for any blockchain
• ✅ [b]Quantum-Resistant[/b] - Post-quantum cryptography (Dilithium5, Kyber1024)
• ✅ [b]Triple-Layer Security[/b] - Network (Tor) + Transport (Noise) + Application (Mixing)
• ✅ [b]Compliance-Ready[/b] - Selective disclosure capabilities for regulations
• ✅ [b]Enterprise SLA[/b] - 99.9% uptime guarantee

[b]Supported Blockchains:[/b]
[code]Bitcoin       - UTXO privacy, CoinJoin enhancement
Ethereum      - MEV protection, private DeFi transactions
Solana        - SPL token privacy, Jupiter swap protection
Litecoin      - Cross-chain atomic swaps with privacy
Dogecoin      - Private transactions for payments
Polygon       - Layer 2 privacy enhancement
Avalanche     - Cross-subnet private routing[/code]

[b]Production SDKs Available:[/b]
• [b]Python SDK[/b] - Bitcoin/Litecoin/Dogecoin (500+ lines, production-ready)
• [b]JavaScript SDK[/b] - Ethereum/Solana/Polygon (450+ lines, Flashbots integration)
• [b]Rust SDK[/b] - Native integration for blockchain projects

[b]Security Model:[/b]
• CLIENT-SIDE SIGNING - Private keys never leave your machine
• IDEMPOTENCY - Safe retries with automatic UUID generation
• RETRY LOGIC - Exponential backoff for network failures

[b]Enterprise Pricing:[/b]
[code]Starter:      $499/month   - 10,000 transactions
Professional: $1,999/month  - 100,000 transactions
Enterprise:   $9,999/month  - Unlimited + dedicated infrastructure[/code]

[b]Developer Integration:[/b]
[code]# Python Bitcoin Example
from q_paas import QNarwhalKnightPaaSClient, BitcoinWallet

wallet = BitcoinWallet(private_key_wif)
client = QNarwhalKnightPaaSClient(api_key)
result = client.mix_bitcoin_transaction(signed_tx)

// JavaScript Ethereum Example
const { QNarwhalKnightPaaSClient, EthereumWallet } = require('q-paas');

const wallet = new EthereumWallet(privateKey, rpcUrl);
const client = new QNarwhalKnightPaaSClient(apiKey);
const result = await client.privateUniswapSwap(wallet, tokenIn, tokenOut, amount);[/code]

