[size=12pt][b]3. AEGIS-QL Post-Quantum Access Control[/b][/size]

Novel cryptographic system for centralized access control with quantum resistance.

[b]Innovation:[/b]
• [b]Sparse Ring-LWE[/b] - Reduces complexity from O(n²) to O(k·n)
• [b]Fast NTT[/b] - O(n log n) polynomial multiplication
• [b]256-bit Security[/b] - 128-bit quantum security
• [b]50-67% Faster[/b] - Compared to NIST PQC standard Kyber-768

[b]Performance Benchmarks:[/b]
[code]Operation       AEGIS-QL    Kyber-768    Improvement
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Key Generation  12,000/s    8,000/s      +50%
Encryption      18,000/s    12,000/s     +50%
Decryption      25,000/s    15,000/s     +67%
Memory Usage    3.2 KB      5.8 KB       -45%[/code]

[b]Access Control Levels:[/b]
[code]Founder   - Full system control (cryptographically enforced)
Admin     - Administrative operations
Operator  - Routine operations
User      - Standard access[/code]

